-- Deutsche Bank to Close Norisbank Branches, Move Online, FTD Says
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-02-07T19:53:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/deutsche-bank-to-close-norisbank-branches-move-online-ftd-says.html
Deutsche Bank AG  plans to close its
Norisbank unit’s 100 branches and move the business online, the
 Financial Times Deutschland  reported in a preview of an article
to be published tomorrow. .  The 400 employees at the unit who will be affected will be
integrated into the branch network of the affiliated Postbank
unit, the newspaper said, citing unidentified people at Deutsche
Bank  Customers will be able to choose if they want to remain
with Norisbank’s online operation or move to Postbank, the FTD
said.  Deutsche Bank spokesman Michael Lermer told Bloomberg News
by telephone that a co-operation agreement has been signed
between Norisbank and Postbank and negotiations with employee
representatives have been scheduled.  To contact the reporter on this story:
